		<td><b>could RetroZone's MMC1 repro board fix this problem...?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So, despite what I said in an earlier post, my R.C. Pro Am cart continues to get scrambled. Sometimes it scrambles, sometimes it doesn't. It always happens on a transition, where bankswitching presumably would be occurring. This leads me to believe that the mapper is faulty. I'm considering getting RetroZone's MMC1 repro board and soldering the PRG and CHR rom chips to it in an attempt to preserve this game. Do you think it might work?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


